anterior being larger"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etwo cusps with the anterior being larger\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct anatomical description of the mitral valve (image). The anterior (aortic) cusp is broader and longer than the posterior cusp, though the posterior cusp has a longer attachment to the annulus. The posterior cusp typically has three scallops.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETwo cusps with the posterior being larger\u003C/strong\u003E - the mitral valve has two cusps, the anterior cusp is larger\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFour cusps of equal size\u003C/strong\u003E - the mitral valve consistently has two cusps\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThree cusps of equal size\u003C/strong\u003E - this describes the tricuspid valve on the right side of the heart\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESingle cusp with multiple attachments\u003C/strong\u003E - the mitral valve requires two cusps for proper function\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe mitral valve apparatus also includes two papillary muscles (anterolateral and posteromedial) with chordae tendineae attaching to both cusps, and the fibrous mitral annulus. This complete structure ensures competent valve function during the cardiac cycle.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The mitral valve has two cusps: anterior (larger) and posterior (smaller with three scallops).","The mitral valve apparatus includes papillary muscles, chordae tendineae, valve cusps and the mitral annulus.","The mitral valve prevents backflow of blood from the left ventricle to the left atrium during systole."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cMitral valve\u201d by Ecgtocardiology\u00a0is licensed under\u00a0Creative Commons Zero, Public Domain Dedication\u00a0license. (http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/deed.en). \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mitral_Valve.png\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65206"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18498"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21402"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21402","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21402"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/JhkP8OheVEoOPBZIllUM1HvU7hDdhZ.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/JhkP8OheVEoOPBZIllUM1HvU7hDdhZ.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":531}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65206","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65206"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-16T11:29:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-16T11:29:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11227"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79910"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","syno